        "4. For most cases, the amount of bad data is much less than good data. How can you mitigate the data imbalance issue?\n",
        "\n",
        "One way you can nitigate this issue is by using metrics like F1 score that will negativly impact your score if you miss a bad data, which is more crucial when theres so few bad data. Also, one could create fake bad data, or remove good data in preprocessing in order to train in a certain way. This makes the model better at spotting bad data and rewards true positives less."
